===Etymology===
{{D.}} ''voor'': advance + ''trekken'': to travel.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

#(Usually plural) A [[Boer]] pioneer, who [[trek]]ked into the hinterland of South Africa during the 1830's.
* The '''Voortrekkers''' left the Cape Colony because of dissatisfaction with English Rule.
#The name of the Afrikaans [[scout]]ing movement.

====Derived terms====
*Voortrekker Monument.
